The paper deals with steganography, which involves hiding information within other data. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), coding theory (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given that the paper focuses on the limitations of steganography and the ability to sample from a channel, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely categories. However, since the paper also presents a new stegosystem, cs.CC and cs.DS are also possible categories. Finally, since steganography is often used in multimedia applications, cs.MM is a less likely but still possible category.
